    "Body": " Associate Procurement Consultant \u2013 Procurement Services IBM - 3.9 Research Triangle Park, NC Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $85,000 - $120,000 a year Qualifications Procurement Microsoft Office Intellectual Property Law Microsoft Powerpoint Microsoft Excel Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description Introduction At IBM, work is more than a job - it's a calling: To build. To design. To code. To consult. To think along with clients and sell. To make markets. To invent. To collaborate. Not just to do something better, but to attempt things you've never thought possible. Are you ready to lead in this new era of technology and solve some of the world's most challenging problems? If so, lets talk. Your Role and Responsibilities IBM is seeking highly motivated individuals with roughly 2-6 years of procurement experience to join our IBM Procurement Services (IPS) team of procurement consulting professionals. IPS provides procurement services to IBM\u2019s external clients across all industry segments. Specifically, we are seeking to fill the role of an Associate Procurement Consultant to support our clients\u2019 procurement and strategic sourcing requirements in indirect spend categories such as: Facilities, MRO, Real Estate, Corporate & Professional Services, Information Technology, and Logistics. This role requires regular business travel to remote client locations based on project requirements, and is based in Research Triangle Park (Raleigh), NC. Responsibilities Managing multiple competitive bid events for client(s) (i.e., Request for Proposal, Request for Quote, Request for Information, Reverse Auctions, etc.) within assigned spend categories Analyzing client\u2019s historical spend data in one or more categories to: identify sourcing opportunities, support category strategy development, and measure compliance with supplier agreements Building and maintaining stakeholder relationships across all levels of the client\u2019s business, procurement, and legal organizations Negotiating commercial terms and facilitating contracting processes with the client\u2019s suppliers Analyzing and documenting cost savings versus historical spend to ensure IBM meets or exceeds contractual savings commitments to our client(s) Identifying opportunities to transform the client\u2019s procurement organization and policies, and to support the client in achieving its strategic business objectives Supporting Global Category Leaders and Category Managers with development of category strategies and developing sourcing project strategies Collaborating with IPS Procurement Consultants supporting our other clients to share and leverage useful templates, strategies, lessons learned, and case studies IBM will not be providing visa sponsorship for these positions now or in the future. Therefore, in order to be considered for this position, you must have the ability to work without a need for current or future visa sponsorship. Required Technical and Professional Expertise Bachelors degree Ability to build rapport with clients & maintain professionalism in communications with all levels of client stakeholders. Delivery of high quality analyses & presentations on time & with the level of quality the client expects. Ability to utilize procurement & financial data to understand spending trends within a business, & to leverage information to identify procurement insights that result in process efficiencies or cost savings for the client. Understanding the necessity & value of accuracy & attention to detail; ability to process information with high levels of accuracy. Strong knowledge & proficiency of Microsoft Office suite. Ability to efficiently & accurately analyze procurement data using Microsoft Excel, & to build client-ready presentations using Microsoft PowerPoint. Knowledge of Procurement methods, technologies and processes. Ability to analyze and improve a client\u2019s procurement organization Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise Prefer previous experience in a client facing / consultative role. About Business Unit IBM Global Procurement has the responsibility for achieving the best overall value for IBM and our clients when acquiring or contracting goods, services, and intellectual property assets. Our mission: \"Listen for need, source with speed.\" We continually work to create value by managing costs and risks, engaging in revenue generation opportunities with our sales teams, and providing superior service to our clients as we ensure on-time delivery. Join us as we transform clients' strategies by delivering simple engagements focused on speed, leveraging digitization, cognitive insights, and innovation from suppliers to maximize value. Your Life @ IBM What matters to you when you\u2019re looking for your next career challenge? Maybe you want to get involved in work that really changes the world? What about somewhere with incredible and diverse career and development opportunities \u2013 where you can truly discover your passion? Are you looking for a culture of openness, collaboration and trust \u2013 where everyone has a voice? What about all of these? If so, then IBM could be your next career challenge. Join us, not to do something better, but to attempt things you never thought possible. Impact. Inclusion. Infinite Experiences. Do your best work ever. About IBM IBM\u2019s greatest invention is the IBMer. We believe that progress is made through progressive thinking, progressive leadership, progressive policy and progressive action. IBMers believe that the application of intelligence, reason and science can improve business, society and the human condition. Restlessly reinventing since 1911, we are the largest technology and consulting employer in the world, with more than 380,000 IBMers serving clients in 170 countries. Location Statement For additional information about location requirements, please discuss with the recruiter following submission of your application. Being You @ IBM IBM is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status. IBM is also committed to compliance with all fair employment practices regarding citizenship and immigration status. "
